As you can see, so
currently we have a hard coded value and

2
00:00:04.640 --> 00:00:08.950
a hard coded color palette.

3
00:00:08.950 --> 00:00:11.000
We would like these to be dynamic.

4
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.510
So what we wanna do is we want
to pass the palette name and

5
00:00:15.510 --> 00:00:17.930
the colors down to
the color palette screen so

6
00:00:17.930 --> 00:00:22.040
it could be extended to render
any color palettes we want.

7
00:00:22.040 --> 00:00:25.550
And you can do this as a second
argument in the navigate prop.

8
00:00:25.550 --> 00:00:29.280
So the first argument is always the name
of the screen you will navigate to,

9
00:00:29.280 --> 00:00:33.040
and the second argument is optional.

10
00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:39.750
But it can be properties that you want to
be passed into the color palette screen.

11
00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:44.710
For screens that you've navigated to,

12
00:00:44.710 --> 00:00:48.225
you get a special route
param added automatically.

13
00:00:48.225 --> 00:00:50.882
So this is out of the same
way as the navigation param.

14
00:00:50.882 --> 00:00:55.971
And these parameters will become
available from route.params.paletteName.

15
00:00:55.971 --> 00:00:58.500
So for example here,
if you do route.params.paletteName,

16
00:00:58.500 --> 00:00:59.510
you will get Solarized.

17
